diff:1531413495:1531285376:=93,94c93%0a%3c The leader of the council. In some jurisdictions the Councilors defer to the Hierarch, acting as her advisors. In others she acts as moderator in hearings but only casts a vote in the event of a tie. Hierarchs usually serve for life unless exceptional circumstances convince them to step down. A Hierarch is usually allowed to name her own successor, unless she leaves the post in disgrace, in which case the Councilors elect the new Hierarch%0a%3c %0a---%0a> %0a100,101d98%0a%3c A member of the council. Traditionally there are four or five Councilors in addition to the Hierarch, and each Path has a single representative. A Councilor usually holds the post until he dies, willingly steps down, retires, or falls out of favor with the rest of the Consilium. The remaining Councilors elect a new member to fill any vacancy.%0a%3c %0a111,112d107%0a%3c Mages tasked with ensuring the council’s orders are carried out. Each member of the council usually appoints a Provost to represent him, and so mages in this post often act as proxies for the Councilor (or Hierarch) they serve.Provosts are the seconds of the councilors they handle the minutiae paperwork and can act in the council members stead if they are unable or too busy to handle matters they are the face to their order.  '''Provost Player must be actively IC (required for all high positions) PC must be doing things to put their order in a good light and working towards completion of mage concerns.''' %0a%3c %0a122,123d116%0a%3c Enforcers appointed by the Hierarch to patrol the Consilium’s sancta and Demesnes and carry out its rulings. The council dispatches a Sentinel whenever a mage or cabal has violated Consilium mandates. If Provosts ensure that member cabals adhere to council instructions, a Sentinel provides them with an incentive to cooperate. She may deliver a polite warning, command an immediate tribunal appearance before the council, or mete out a stern punishment — depending on the severity of the transgression and the orders of the Consilium.  Deputy Sentinels or just Sentinels are those who are in charge of bringing those who break the laws and edicts to justice they are the first line of defense of the consilia and it's members.%0a%3c %0a133,134d125%0a%3c Ambassadors and messengers of the Consilium, appointed by the Hierarch. Heralds deliver news and general announcements to member cabals and represent the Consilium to other Consilia. They frequently welcome new arrivals to the region and ensure they are aware of Consilium rules.%0a%3c %0a141,142d131%0a%3c '''Must have academics 4 Occult 5''' Scribes are the recorders of what happens in the consilia the keepers of creative thaumaturgies created and weilded by the mages of the city and the keepers of that knowledge.%0a%3c %0a149,150d137%0a%3c '''Factotums Need Academics 3 and be completely familiar with the laws of the consilia'''. They are the law keepers and prosecutors and defenders of those accused of breaking the laws.%0a%3c %0a159,160d145%0a%3c %0a%3c Masked executors of justice who carry out the sentences the Consilium passes. Only a Guardian of the Veil can hold this post, and most Interfectors serve all the Consilia within the local Guardian Caucus.  Interfectors are the Right hand of the Consilium when punishment is to be meted out it is the Interfector who performs it. Be it Soul Scourging or The Like it is their solemn duty to uphold the laws edicts and judgement of the consilia.  '''Sentinel Deputy must have applicable combat and investigation or infiltration skills.  Interfector must be active GoV and completed one mission at GoV behest.'''%0a
