diff:1528498530:1528475908:=3,10c3%0a%3c ----%0a%3c !%25center%25'''Mage Venue'''%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c %25center%25''"I think becoming a wizard is about discovering what’s real and what isn’t."'' \\%0a%3c %25center%25- '''Ben Aaronovich, Midnight Riot''' - \\%0a%3c \\%0a%3c %0a---%0a> %0a12,23c5,11%0a%3c [[#top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !The Orders%0a%3c %0a%3c Although smaller, isolated groups of mages cling on in some parts of the world, catering to regional interests or unwholesome practices other mages frown upon, the global society of magic is largely divided among six great Orders. Each Order is made p of thousands of smaller organizations with attached mystery cults, secret societies, and associations that give them an occult “footprint” in the Fallen World. Although most Sleeper occultists wouldn’t know them by name, those “in the know” are aware that the Orders exist even if only by rumor and inference.%0a%3c %0a%3c Even the youngest Order contains magical societies tracing their teachings to the Stone Age, and the eldest are more than two millennia old. Without common cause with an Order, a mage is bereft of vast accumulated knowledge and influence, which the Orders are happy to leverage when recruiting. %0a%3c %0a%3c The four Orders of the Diamond share common origins and a philosophy based around molding themselves after the Supernal symbols of magical society in the Time Before, taking on the roles of mages in that vanished utopia as a means to power. %0a%3c %0a%3c !!Adamantine Arrows%0a%3c %0a---%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> !!The Orders%0a> %0a> !Adamantine Arrows%0a> %0a30,33c18,21%0a%3c [[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Free Council%0a%3c %0a---%0a> [&#8593; back to top]%0a> %0a> !Free Council%0a> %0a46,49c34,37%0a%3c [[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Guardians of the Veil%0a%3c %0a---%0a> [&#8593; back to top]%0a> %0a> !Guardians of the Veil%0a> %0a58,60c46,48%0a%3c [[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !!''Mysterium''%0a---%0a> [&#8593; back to top]%0a> %0a> !Mysterium%0a69,71c57,59%0a%3c [[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !!''Silver Ladder''%0a---%0a> [&#8593; back to top]%0a> %0a> !Silver Ladder%0a82,89c70,73%0a%3c [[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !'''The Consilium'''%0a%3c %0a%3c Wherever many mages gather in a region with a compelling long-term Mystery or many smaller Mysteries, the danger of conflict arises. Cabals dispute control of resources and real estate, to say nothing of access to contested Mysteries. The Pentacle manages these pressures by creating a Consilium — a panel of Councilors chaired by a Hierarch, who hear and resolve disputes. Consilium decisions are backed up by social pressure — cabals who don’t agree to abide by their local Consilium don’t get the protection from other mages it affords. Also, the judges tend to come from the oldest, most powerful cabals and employ Sentinels — enforcers and detectives who levy out the Consilium’s punishments. A Consilium’s decisions aren’t always final — Convocations can act as a court of appeal — and they aren’t there to act as a government, except in issues where they make rulings to protect every Pentacle mage in their territory. As long as it doesn’t break any local laws, what a cabal gets up to is entirely the business of its members.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> [&#8593; back to top]%0a> %0a> !!The Consilium%0a> %0a131,137c115,120%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !'''Lex Magica'''%0a%3c %0a%3c !!''The Major Laws''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> [&#8593; back to top]%0a> %0a> !Lex Magica%0a> %0a> The Major Laws%0a> %0a140,141c123,124%0a%3c !!''Rite of Acceptance''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Rite of Acceptance%0a> %0a144,145c127,128%0a%3c !!''Rite of Wisdom''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Rite of Wisdom%0a> %0a148,149c131,132%0a%3c !!''Rite of Crossing''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Rite of Crossing%0a> %0a152,153c135,136%0a%3c !!''Rite of Hospitality''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Rite of Hospitality%0a> %0a156,157c139,140%0a%3c !!''Rite of Sanctum''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Rite of Sanctum%0a> %0a161,162c144,145%0a%3c !'''The Minor Rose Laws'''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> !The Minor Rose Laws%0a> %0a165,166c148,149%0a%3c !!''The Tenet of the Veil''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The Tenet of the Veil%0a> %0a177,178c160,161%0a%3c !!''The Tenet of Hubris''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The Tenet of Hubris%0a> %0a189,190c172,173%0a%3c !!''The Tenet of Protection''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The Tenet of Protection%0a> %0a199,200c182,183%0a%3c !!''The Tenet of War''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The Tenet of War%0a> %0a209,215c192,197%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !'''Sanctions'''%0a%3c %0a%3c !!''Minor Reprimand''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> [&#8593; back to top]%0a> %0a> !Sanctions%0a> %0a> Minor Reprimand%0a> %0a218,219c200,201%0a%3c !!''Major Reprimand''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Major Reprimand%0a> %0a222c204,205%0a%3c !!''Payment of Debt''%0a---%0a> Payment of Debt%0a> %0a225,226c208,209%0a%3c !!''Minor Penance''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Minor Penance%0a> %0a229,230c212,213%0a%3c !!''Major Penance''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Major Penance%0a> %0a233,234c216,217%0a%3c !!''Severe Reprimand''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Severe Reprimand%0a> %0a236,238c219,220%0a%3c %0a%3c !!''Incarceration''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Incarceration%0a> %0a241,242c223,224%0a%3c !!''Banishment''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Banishment%0a> %0a245,246c227,228%0a%3c !!''Spiritual Scourging''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Spiritual Scourging%0a> %0a248,249c230%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a---%0a> [&#8593; back to top]%0a
